---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Introduction - Worker Image CDN">
	<h1>Worker Image CDN</h1>
	<p>A Cloudflare Worker that acts as an image CDN proxy. It fetches images from an origin server, automatically converts them to modern formats, resizes on the fly, and caches the results in R2.</p>

	<h2>Features</h2>
	<table>
		<thead>
			<tr>
				<th>Feature</th>
				<th>Description</th>
			</tr>
		</thead>
		<tbody>
			<tr>
				<td><strong>Automatic format conversion</strong></td>
				<td>Serves AVIF or WebP based on the browser's <code>Accept</code> header</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td><strong>On-the-fly resizing</strong></td>
				<td>Resize via query parameters, preserving aspect ratio</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td><strong>Quality control</strong></td>
				<td>Adjust output quality with <code>?quality=80</code></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td><strong>R2 caching</strong></td>
				<td>Transformed images are cached in Cloudflare R2</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td><strong>Step snapping</strong></td>
				<td>Dimensions and quality snap to configured steps for efficient caching</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td><strong>SVG passthrough</strong></td>
				<td>SVGs are served as-is without conversion</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td><strong>Cache observability</strong></td>
				<td><code>X-Cache: HIT/MISS</code> header</td>
			</tr>
		</tbody>
	</table>

	<h2>How it works</h2>
	<pre><code>Request → Check R2 cache → [HIT]  → Serve cached image
                        → [MISS] → Fetch from origin
                                  → Resize (if requested)
                                  → Convert to AVIF/WebP
                                  → Store in R2
                                  → Serve image</code></pre>

	<h2>Quick start</h2>
	<pre><code>npm install
npx wrangler r2 bucket create worker-cdn-images
npm run dev</code></pre>
	<p>Then request an image:</p>
	<pre><code>http://localhost:8787/photo.jpg?w=800&quality=80</code></pre>
</Layout>
